1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
What if I told you a simple sugar can transform into alcohol?

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,400
This is called alcoholic fermentation, a process used for centuries in brewing and baking.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,400
It all starts with yeast.

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:16,800
This tiny fungus munches on sugar, producing alcohol and carbon dioxide.

5
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,600
But not all yeast acts the same.

6
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,800
Different strains yield different flavors and alcohol levels.

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:29,200
So, next time you enjoy a drink, remember that tiny organisms worked magic behind the scenes.

8
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:31,200
Curious about more science secrets?

9
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,200
Like and follow for more!
